name: Pepe Resistance Card (PRC)
description:
Series: 1  
Card: 10  
Artist: Rey

Pepe the Frog has become more than just a meme, he has become a symbol of hope and resistance. In 2019, the people of Hong Kong took to the streets to protest against the Chinese government's extradition bill, which threatened their autonomy and freedom.

This card is a commemoration and homage to the Hong Kong protests where Pepe became the face of the resilience of the human spirit and the power of community to come together and create positive change.

Raise your fist in solidarity with Pepe the Frog, as we continue to work towards a brighter future for all.

name: Pepefucius
description:
Series: 1  
Card: 12  
Artist: Looks Rare

c. 551 - 479 BCE

A Kekistan philosopher and politician of the Spring and Autumn period who is traditionally considered the paragon of Kek sages. Pepefucius's teachings and philosophy underpin Far East Kekistan culture and society remaining influential to this day.

His philosophical teachings, called Pepefucianism, emphasized personal and governmental morality, correctness of social relationships, justice, kindness, and sincerity.

He espoused the Golden Rule, 'do not do unto other Pepes what you do not want done to yourself.'

name: DEyes #333
description:
Generative edition celebrating the Decentral Eyes OG portrait series.
This edition uses 12 layers to create 623 unique 1/1 portrait artworks featuring 9 faces who have shaped the early days of the decentralized blockchain revolution. 

Vitalik Buterin
Andreas Antonopoulos
John McAfee
Edward Snowden
Julian Assange
Tyler and Cameron Winklevoss
Dalai Lama
Warren Buffett
Alan Turing

9 is the number of completion. It represents the end of this cycle and the beginning of the next cycle.

The edition number of 623 is a symbolic number that represents the first time I publically displayed any version of the Decentral Eyes series. A physical print version of the Vitalik Buterin portrait at the NAC crypto conference in San Francisco on 6/23/18 was the genesis release date.

What a long, strange trip it's been.

signatures.message: I, Coldie have issued an Async Art Blueprint "DecentralEyesMashup" on contract address 0xc143bbfcdbdbed6d454803804752a064a622c1f3 with an edition count of 623.

name: ART👑KING #063
description:
Art history meets the blockchain

The rediscovery and redefinition of traditional classical art in a contemporary interpretation in the NFT era characterize my artistic path, which combines the spirit and styles of past masterpieces with new digital techniques.
These generative tokens are the evolution of "the Remixable" series released on Async.Art Gallery since september 2020.

Unique NFTs generated by the remix of 10 paintings by masters of the history of Art:
Antonello da Messina - ritratto d'uomo (1475-76), Sandro Botticelli - alleged self-portrait (1475), Raffaello Sanzio - ritratto di Agnolo Doni (1506), Tiziano - ritratto di Carlo V (1533-35), Sofonisba Anguissola - ritratto di Alessandro Farnese (1560), Caravaggio - Bacco (1596-98), Rembrandt - self portrait (1640), Giovan Battista Tiepolo - frescoes in the Würzburg residenz, detail (1751-53), Paul Cézanne - portrait de Victor Chocquet (1876-77), Vincent van Gogh - self-portrait (1889)
+ rare traits from 'Satoshi Nakamoto' face as the symbolic father of Bitcoin and blockchains.

618 tokens edition out of 3513840 possible generative iterations
2 styles, 14 layers with varying degrees of rarity
3 animated MP4 legendary editions
1200x1200px png portraits

name: Forest Trash and Treasure #100
description:
Decay is part of the natural cycle of the forest. Detritus is a natural source of regeneration and sustenance for the flora and fauna. But something is happening. Not all detritus is of the forest. Other forms of dead and discarded materials have become a harmful interruption to what nature has intended and the cycle is corrupted... at least the starry skies above remain free from it all... or do they..?


This project is another @aliasrubytuesday, @sambearsays-climatefund and @sambearsays-nftfootprintfund collaboration (see also "Sam Bear Says" project). 33.33% of the artist’s sales share will go towards climate action projects and a further 33.33% towards NFT carbon footprint reduction projects. This will be collected in the sambearsays-climatefund* and the sambearsays-nftfootprintfund* collaborative artists' accounts, respectively.
